div id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Ἀθανίππου \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΑΘΑΝΙΠΠΟΥ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004421_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004421_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004421.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004421-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text as per Sofia 2018\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>(tomb) of Athanippos\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph consists of a single name in the genitive, as with the majority of the epitaphs attested from this necropolis. The name \u003Ca href=\"http://www.lgpn.ox.ac.uk/name/%E1%BC%88%CE%B8%CE%AC%CE%BD%CE%B9%CF%80%CF%80%CE%BF%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Ἀθάνιππος\u003C/a> is not a common one, with only one other known (probably) Sicilian instance (IG II/III (2nd edn) 10293: Ἕρμων | Ἀθανίππου | Σικελὸς | ἀπὸ Τυνδαρίδος, a funerary inscription from Athens of the imperial period.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Sofia 2018 108 no.11 and fig.12 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Plainly cut and fairly regular squarish letters. Alpha has broken bar (and in the first instance, shows a slight apex at the top); theta is smaller than other letters and mid-line, with a single central dot; nu has equal length vertical strokes (the right slightly off vertical); pi is quadrate in form with nearly equal length vertical strokes and slightly overlapping horizontal; omicron is slightly smaller than other letters and mid-line.\u003C/p> Line 1  29  Interlineation line 1 to 2  NA  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  \u003C/div>",[186,189,192,195,198,201,204,207],{"id":187,"html":188},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Ἀθανίππου \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΑΘΑΝΙΠΠΟΥ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":190,"html":191},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004421_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004421_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004421.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004421-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":193,"html":194},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text as per Sofia 2018\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":196,"html":197},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>(tomb) of Athanippos\u003C/p>  ",{"id":199,"html":200},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph consists of a single name in the genitive, as with the majority of the epitaphs attested from this necropolis. The name \u003Ca href=\"http://www.lgpn.ox.ac.uk/name/%E1%BC%88%CE%B8%CE%AC%CE%BD%CE%B9%CF%80%CF%80%CE%BF%CF%82\" target=\"_blank\">Ἀθάνιππος\u003C/a> is not a common one, with only one other known (probably) Sicilian instance (IG II/III (2nd edn) 10293: Ἕρμων | Ἀθανίππου | Σικελὸς | ἀπὸ Τυνδαρίδος, a funerary inscription from Athens of the imperial period.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":202,"html":203},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Sofia 2018 108 no.11 and fig.12 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\" targ