            \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!--from Sofia 2018-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">121\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">29\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">12\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>A single line of Greek letters filling the width of the stele, approximately 20 cm from the top of the stele.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Plainly cut and fairly regular squarish letters. Alpha has broken bar (and in the first instance, shows a slight apex at the top); theta is smaller than other letters and mid-line, with a single central dot; nu has equal length vertical strokes (the right slightly off vertical); pi is quadrate in form with nearly equal length vertical strokes and slightly overlapping horizontal; omicron is slightly smaller than other letters and mid-line.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"29\" atMost=\"29\">29\u003C/height>\u003C!--from Sofia 2018-->\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\">NA\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462062\" corresp=\"#findspot\">Abacaenum\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003Coffset>near\n                                    \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2522853\">Tripi\u003C/placeName>\n                                \u003C/offset>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>38.05191, 15.10158\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0350\" notAfter-custom=\"-0201\" evidence=\"archaeological-context\">The tomb has not been excavated, but the cemetery went out of use around the end of the 3rd century BCE, offering a terminus ante quem\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" xml:id=\"findspot\">Unnumbered tomb on the eastern margin of the excavated area of the necropolis (close to tomb 23) \n                            in contrada Cardusa\u003Cgeo>38.065190, 15.114380\u003C/geo>, where it remains in situ\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">Metcalfe 2016 visited site\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                 \u003Cchange when=\"2020-05-28\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag created the file from template, publications, and photographs\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2020-09-10\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n            \t\t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n\t    \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-21\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic004421_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic004421.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>Ἀθανίππου\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n               \u003ClistApp>\n                   \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>text as per Sofia 2018\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n              \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>(tomb) of Athanippos\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>The epitaph consists of a single name in the genitive, as with the majority of the epitaphs attested from this necropolis. The name \u003Cref target=\"http://www.lgpn.ox.ac.uk/name/%E1%BC%88%CE%B8%CE%AC%CE%BD%CE%B9%CF%80%CF%80%CE%BF%CF%82\">Ἀθάνιππος\u003C/ref> is not a common one, with only one other known (probably) Sicilian instance (IG II/III (2nd edn) 10293: Ἕρμων | Ἀθανίππου | Σικελὸς | ἀπὸ Τυνδαρίδος, a funerary inscription from Athens of the imperial period.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                   \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Sofia\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2018\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>108 no.11 and fig.12\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/JQQKI6JP\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
